commit message: Added docs about Weblate and translation shield.
Move 'differences' to the bottom of the README.

Merge pull request #12 from pserwylo/translation-instructions

Added Weblate translation instructions
Add percentage after total score.

Merge pull request #14 from pserwylo/fix-10--add-percentage

Add percentage after total score.

Adding initial tests to trie library.

Having good test coverage of the trie library will make it less scary
to start refactoring in order to support multiple languages beyond US
and UK English.
Moved TrieBuilder to trie library from trie-builder.
Extract test utils methods to own class.
Extracted common test functions into base class.

Add test for full uk and us dictionaries.

Unfortunately, they don't run in Android Studio due to the bug at:

https://code.google.com/p/android/issues/detail?id=64887

Not sure what the progress on that issue is, but these tests run to
completion fine on the command line using:

`gradle :libraries:trie:test`
Add testing notes to README
Update links in README
Add support for Travis CI.

Disable missing translation lint check.

It seems unlikely that this project will always have 100% of translations,
so lets not enforce it.
Add Travis CI shield to README.
Fix lint errors from Android Studio and gradle lint
Don't fail on lint, as Travis CI doesn't have the right platform-tools installed.
